
@startuml
skinparam classAttributeIconName true

class Location {
  -address: String
}

class Driver {
  -firstName: String
  -lastName: String
  +assignOrder(order: Order): void
  +unassignOrder(): void
}

class Vehicle {
  -vehicleNumber: String
  +assignDriver(driver: Driver): void
  +unassignDriver(): void
}

class Truck extends Vehicle {
  -weight: Double
}

class Car extends Vehicle {
  -seats: Integer
}

class Van extends Vehicle {
  // No additional attributes required
}

class Order {
  -origin: Location
  -destination: Location
  -date: Date
  -driver: Driver
  +assignDriver(driver: Driver): void
}

' Associations
Driver "1" *-- "0..1" Vehicle : drives
Driver "1" *-- "1" Order : carries out
Order "1" -- "1" Location : origin
Order "1" -- "1" Location : destination
Vehicle "1" -- "0..1" Driver : assigned to
@enduml

### Explanation of the Diagram:
- **`Location`** has an address.
- **`Driver`** has a first and last name. They can carry out at most one order at a time and are assigned to one vehicle.
- **`Vehicle`** is the base class with a `vehicleNumber`. It is extended by `Truck`, `Car`, and `Van`, each adding their own specific attribute (weight, seats).
- **`Order`** must have an origin and destination location, a date, and at least one driver assigned to it.
- A **driver can be assigned to only one vehicle**, and a **vehicle can be driven by only one driver** at a time.
- An **order is carried out by exactly one driver**, but a **driver can carry out at most one order at any given time**.

